thread.title: N.J. Swing Bridge Fails to Close, Disrupting Morning Commute

author: Paul Berger
title: N.J. Swing Bridge Fails to Close, Disrupting Morning Commute
text:
Tens of thousands of rail commuters faced disruption Friday morning when a century-old swing bridge in New Jersey failed to close.
The swing bridge, which crosses the Hackensack River at Kearny, N.J., is an infrequent cause of delays on the Northeast Corridor, the busiest rail line in the nation connecting Washington, D.C. and Boston.
